The paper deals with data structures and algorithms for efficiently finding induced ancestors and longest common substrings, which are topics commonly studied in computer science subfields such as data structures (cs.DS), computational geometry (cs.CG), discrete mathematics (cs.DM), information theory (cs.IT), and machine learning (cs.DL). However, since the paper focuses on data structures and algorithms, it is most likely to belong to the cs.DS sub-category.
